The table below represents the results of a reaction to produce ethanol by reacting methanol, carbon dioxide, and hydrogen gas. Not all the methanol is reacted. There is a competing reaction which produces acetic acid. For your information (this is not necesary to solve the problems), the reactions are given below:

\(CH_3OH\:+\:CO\:+\:2H_2\:\rightarrow\:C_2H_5OH\:+\:H_2O\)
\(CH_3OH\:+\:CO\:\rightarrow\:CH_3COOH\)

Calculate the
- \(Conversion\:of\:Methanol\),
- \(Selectivity\:for\:Ethanol\), and
- \(Yield\:of\:Ethanol\)
for this reaction.


\(Conversion\:(\%)\) \(Selectivity\:(\%)\) \(Yield\:(\%)\)

Carbon Dioxide 419 251
Hydrogen Gas 838 697
Water 0 70
Ethanol 0 70

questiontext.text: The diagram below shows a counter current heat exchanger. \(T_{hot}in = 81°C\), \(T_{hot}out = 49°C\), \(T_{cold}in = 31°C\), and \(T_{cold}out = 46°C\). The flow of the hot stream is \(m_H\;=\; 2.1 kg/s\). The heat capacity of the hot stream is \(=\;1160 J/kg/°C\). Calculate the UA value for the heat exchanger. Give your answer in W/°C. Just give the number, don’t include the units in your answer.

generalfeedback.text: The UA value is given by \(UA \; = \; q/LMTD\) where \(q \; = \; m_H\times C_H\times (T_{Hot}in - T_{Hot}out)\) and \(LMTD \; = \; \frac{(\Delta T_{left} - \Delta T_{right})}{log_e(\Delta T_{left}/\Delta T_{left})}\)
